eting narrative voice, Fraser interweaves these examples with his own past-including his false arrest on charges of planning to blow up the Liberty Bell during the Civil Rights era-to tell a story both urgent and timeless.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aElite (Social sciences)zUnited StatesxHistory. 0aIncome distributionzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aPower (Social sciences)zUnited StatesxHistory. 0aProtest movementszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSocial conflictzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSocial psychologyzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235302423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300235302.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles